    "claim": "The referral gate relies on `extcodesize == 0` via `notContract(referrer)`, but contracts in construction also report zero code size. A contract factory can therefore register a contract-controlled referrer during its constructor even though the code tries to exclude contract referrers.",
    "impact": "If the referral mapping is used for payouts, tiers, airdrops, or other economic benefits, attackers can sybil-farm referral slots with contract wallets despite the intended anti-bot restriction, weakening referral integrity and any downstream accounting that trusts this state.",
    "paths": [
      "Deploy a contract whose constructor triggers `deposit(..., referrer)`.",
      "Use a referrer address that is also still in construction, so `notContract(referrer)` returns true.",
      "The constructor call stores `referrals[msg.sender] = referrer`, permanently registering a contract-controlled referral relationship."
    ]
  },
