    "claim": "The \"new user\" check in `processReferrals` only looks at the caller's current balances in four hardcoded pools (`usdc`, `usdt`, `dai`, `wbtcSwappLP`). Users who previously participated and fully withdrew, or who already staked some other allowed token address, are still treated as referral-eligible on a later deposit.",
    "impact": "Any referral rewards or user segmentation built on this mapping can be manipulated: existing users can wait, fully exit, and later backfill a referrer, while users who already interacted through other token pools can still claim first-time referral status. That distorts referral attribution and any reward budget tied to it.",
